The <b>Cavalier Parliament</b> of <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../316/9316.xml">
England</link></country>
 lasted from <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../353/19353.xml">
May 8</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../588/34588.xml">
1661</link> until <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../954/15954.xml">
January 24</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../655/38655.xml">
1679</link>. It followed the <parliament wordnetid="108319198" confidence="0.8">
<social_group wordnetid="107950920" confidence="0.8">
<assembly wordnetid="108163792" confidence="0.8">
<meeting wordnetid="108307589" confidence="0.8">
<gathering wordnetid="107975026" confidence="0.8">
<convention wordnetid="108309086" confidence="0.8">
<group wordnetid="100031264" confidence="0.8">
<legislature wordnetid="108163273" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../756/220756.xml#xpointer(//*[./st=%22Convention+Parliament+of+1660%22])">
Convention Parliament</link></legislature>
</group>
</convention>
</gathering>
</meeting>
</assembly>
</social_group>
</parliament>
. It endured for over 17 years of the quarter century reign of <sovereign wordnetid="110628644" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../688/46688.xml">
Charles II of England</link></person>
</sovereign>
. Like its predecessor <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../033/378033.xml">
Parliament of England</link>, it was overwhelmingly <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../563/484563.xml">
Royalist</link> and is also known as the <b>Pensionary Parliament</b> for the many <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../613/43613.xml">
pension</link>s it granted to adherents of the King.<p>

It was responsible for enacting the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../212/175212.xml">
Clarendon Code</link>, including:
